    "Both historians emphasized the outer perimeter or frame as the key to Romanesque composition, what he termed in <em>La stylistique ornementale dans la sculpture romane</em> the \"Law of the Frame.\"": [],
    "The Romanesque stylized its treatment of objects rather than attempting to be true to nature.": [],
    "Linear designs, he contended, are derived from plant forms, which reveal an intellectual conception.": [],
    "The saints and beasts of the Romanesque belong were transformed into a decorative and conceptual design belonging to the architectural order from which they sprang (Sypher).": [
